  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Tower Crane Operator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>JOB PURPOSE</strong></u></p><ul><li>Report to the immediate supervisor as well as attend a daily toolbox meeting and, understanding the requirements of the job as discussed in the meeting, whilst taking note of any safety instructions and precautions.</li></ul><p><u><strong>EDUCATION/ PROFESSIONAL QUALIFICATION (S)</strong></u></p><ul><li>Secondary school certificate or above.</li></ul><p><u><strong>WORKING EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least 2 years of relevant experience in crane operation and maintenance.</li></ul><p><u><strong>COMPETENCIES</strong></u></p><ul><li>Understanding crane signal.</li><li>Understanding of crane operating.</li><li>Crane equipment repair & servicing</li></ul><p><u><strong>JOB DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></u></p><ul><li>Understand the proper procedures of crane operating.</li><li>Follow instructions from superiors and carry out tasks in a safe and productive manner.</li><li>Know and maintain the acceptable standard and quality of work under the codes.</li><li>Maintain tools, equipment, and materials.</li><li>Inspect crane and equipment and ensure that good condition is maintained at the workplace.</li><li>Maintain well timekeeping and discipline at the workplace.</li><li>Inspect the work done and obtain the supervisor approval.</li><li>Ensure that all safety procedures and regulations are complied with, as defined in the Safety and Health Manual.</li><li>If any incident occurs in workplace, employee should report to supervisor before leaving the yard.</li><li>Promote safe working procedures to prevent accidents.</li><li>Perform work safely and utilize safety equipment properly, follow yard safety rules and regulations and report any lapses in safety procedures.</li></ul><p><u><strong>LOCATION</strong></u></p><ul><li>Seatrium Shipyard (Tuas/Tuas Boulevard/Gul/Benoi)</li><li>Bus transport provided at selected MRT stations (pick-up/drop off)</li></ul>",
